  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (COMPOUND-03 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across all five flow-speed combinations; seven of thirteen credibility factors were formally assessed and six remain as acknowledged epistemic gaps. The assessment team concluded that the aggregated evidence, including a comprehensive mesh-refinement study and three independent validation datasets, supports a Medium assurance level and the simulation package was accepted for regulatory submission. [ADVERSARIAL NOTE: assuranceLevel is declared Medium while W-AR-02 fires — Discretization error achievedLevel 1 < requiredLevel 3 with outcome Accepted, making the Medium declaration unsupported and triggering COMPOUND-03.]",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "VAD use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class III",
  "modelRiskLevel": 5,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5",
